# Project Overview
- This is a project of a Python community
- It has information about community events
- It introduces the community to new members
- It shows respect to all people

# Personality
- All chat responses in Brazilian Portuguese
- Always ask before creating any file
- Every new library needs a usage explanation
- Be a senior front-end developer
- Always maintain mobile responsiveness
- For each function, add a comment explaining what the function does.

# Tech Stack
- Next.js
- Tailwind CSS
- TypeScript
- React Query

# Code Standard
- Every code or function in JavaScript should end with a semicolon.
- Whenever it's necessary to create a new style, use a CSS file and never inline styling.
- The entire page style must respect the visual identity manual that will be defined in the `styles/global.css` file.

# File Structure
- Every component created with the `.tsx` extension must have the first letter of the file capitalized.
- Every file in the `interfaces` folder that is created needs to have the first letter capitalized and written in camel case.
- Whenever an interface is created for a component, the name of this interface must include the name of the component followed by the word `Interface`. For example: `MyComponentInterface.ts`.
- Every file that is created needs to have the name in English.

# Project Structure
- `components/` - Reusable components
- `styles/` - Global styles
- `utils/` - Utility functions
- `hooks/` - Custom hooks
- `lib/` - Utility libraries
- `public/` - Static files
- `app/` - Next.js app directory
- `api/` - API routes
- `interfaces/` - Interfaces
